'''日本趣味'''（'''Japonaiserie'''）是荷蘭畫家[[文森特·梵高|文森特·梵高]]發明的一個詞語，用來表達[[日本主義|日本主義]]對當代歐洲藝術的影響。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/search/advanced?originaltext=original&term=Japonaiserie&person_terms=&person_code=&literature_terms=&literature_code=&workofart_terms=&workofart_code=&bibleref_terms=&bibleref_code=&f_number=&jh_number=&periodical=&from=1&id_range=&id_type=jlb_id&date_from=1872-09-29&date_until=1890-07-31&period=&correspondent_name=&correspondent_id=&place_name=&place_id=&order=date&search2.x=13&search2.y=8&search2=Search |title=Search result |work=Vincent van Gogh. The Letters |publisher=[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]] |location=Amsterdam |access-date=2015-11-11 |archive-date=2017-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009041410/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/search/advanced?originaltext=original&term=Japonaiserie&person_terms=&person_code=&literature_terms=&literature_code=&workofart_terms=&workofart_code=&bibleref_terms=&bibleref_code=&f_number=&jh_number=&periodical=&from=1&id_range=&id_type=jlb_id&date_from=1872-09-29&date_until=1890-07-31&period=&correspondent_name=&correspondent_id=&place_name=&place_id=&order=date&search2.x=13&search2.y=8&search2=Search |dead-url=no }}</ref> 在[[黑船事件|黑船事件]]之前，荷蘭是僅有的對日貿易商，在此之後日本與西方的交流日漸增多，而梵高也因此受到了影響。

梵高和[[馬奈|馬奈]]、[[莫奈|莫奈]]等其他藝術家一樣開始收集日本的[[浮世繪|浮世繪]]作品，梵高實際還和弟弟[[西奧·梵高_(商人)|西奧]]做過一段時間的浮世繪買賣生意，並收集了上百幅浮世繪。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vangoghmuseum.nl/vgm/index.jsp?page=206701&lang=en |title=Japanese prints: Catalogue of the Van Gogh Museum’s collection |publisher=[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]] |location=Amsterdam |access-date=2015-11-11 |archive-date=2011-07-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727025644/http://www.vangoghmuseum.nl/vgm/index.jsp?page=206701&lang=en |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let620/letter.html |title=Letter 620 |work=Vincent van Gogh. The Letters |publisher=[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]] |location=Amsterdam |access-date=2015-11-11 |archive-date=2020-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200812014307/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let620/letter.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 因此梵高對日本藝術產生了興趣，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let545/letter.html |title=Letter 545 |work=Vincent van Gogh. The Letters |publisher=[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]] |location=Amsterdam |access-date=2015-11-11 |archive-date=2020-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807234428/http://www.vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let545/letter.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 1887年時，梵高繪製的作品《藝伎（仿英泉）》即是受了日本浮世繪畫家[[溪齋英泉|溪齋英泉]]影響，此外當年他還仿繪過兩幅[[歌川廣重|歌川廣重]]的作品。

